---
alwaysApply: true
globs: "**/*.ts"
---

# ANGULAR 21 RULES

- Use standalone components by default
- Use signals for local state
- Use RxJS for async streams

- Dependency injection:
  - prefer inject() over constructor injection

- Avoid:
  - legacy NgModules (unless required)
  - manual subscriptions without cleanup

# COMPONENT DESIGN

- Components should:
  - be small
  - represent one responsibility
  - avoid business logic

- Move logic to:
  - services
  - signal stores

# TEMPLATE RULES

- Prefer:
  - structural directives (@if, @for)
  - standalone pipes if needed

- Avoid complex template logic

# STYLING

- Tailwind CSS preferred
- No custom CSS unless necessary
- Keep class lists readable

# REACTIVITY MODEL

- signals → UI state
- RxJS → async/data streams